# Local development configuration is handled automatically inside `devenv shell`:
#
#   - Real secrets (OIDC_CLIENT_ID, OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET) are resolved from
#     OpenBao via secretspec (see secretspec.toml).
#   - Host-specific URLs (APP_BASE_URL, FRONTEND_BASE_URL, CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS,
#     VITE_API_BASE, ...) are derived from DEV_HOST.
#   - Non-secret constants (BIND_ADDR) and DATABASE_URL are set by devenv.nix.
#
# So for single-machine local dev you normally do NOT need any .env file.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cross-machine testing
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# To run the dev servers on this machine and use them from another device's
# browser, the URLs must point at this machine's LAN IP (a remote browser
# resolves "localhost" to itself). Create a git-ignored .env.local with:
#
#   DEV_HOST=192.168.1.20
#
# devenv re-derives all the URLs from that. You must also register
# http://192.168.1.20:8080/auth/callback on the Keycloak/OIDC client, otherwise
# the login redirect is rejected. DEV_HOST defaults to "localhost".
